    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. you mention it was \"disastrous\" because of the lack of an exit plan, but what about the initial objective of preventing a potential massacre in Benghazi? wouldn't some argue that the immediate humanitarian success of preventing a mass slaughter is a valid metric of success, even if the long-term political outcome was messy?",
