    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that seems like a very rigid way to look at it though. if we judge every foreign policy action solely on whether it provides perfect long-term stability, it feels like we'd end up with a policy of total non-interventionism. isn't it also a valid strategic interest for major powers to prevent regional chaos or humanitarian catastrophes before they escalate? isn't that just a part of maintaining a stable international order?",
